===== Your "~mods" Folder =====

CAUTION:
	I have no official association or contact with the mod author.
	These guides are UNOFFICIAL.


Notes:
    * This file contains information about what should and can be in your "/mods" folder.
    * Files in your mods folder that are not listed here are likely to cause issues, unless you know exactly what you are doing.
    * Use this to eliminate potential issues with your setup.
    * If file listing ends with (pak,ucas,utoc) that means you need all three of the files.
    * At this stage, this is based on the AIO version of MHM (not individual modules version), but is still largely applicable (TODO)


====================================================================
For a standard MHM AIO setup, without additional mods/addons/patches
====================================================================
	 your "~mods" folder should contain ~ONLY~ the following:
		LNA01_99_P.pak
		LocalizationDB_P.(pak,ucas,utoc)	<-- (from MHM_AIO, not from any other mod)
		zzzzzzz_MHMTextures0z_P.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		zzzzzzz_MHM_Interface0z_P.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		OXA0X.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		OXA01_P.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		OXA02_P.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		Simple_ModLoader.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		Simple_ModLoader_0_P.pak
		zz_FactionsPatch_Textures_P.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		ZZ_Mutant_Loot_Textures_P.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		ZZZ_ProjectItemization-Textures_P.(pak,ucas,utoc)
		zzzzzzz_MHM_2.0_AIO_Full_Standard.pak    --OR--    zzzzzzz_MHM_2.0_AIO_Full_Hardcore.pak


==============================================================
For a MHM install that includes additional mods/patches/addons
==============================================================
Consult the chart at the end to find out what's missing, or what should not be there.

  * If you have files in your "~mods" folder that are not in this list, make sure you know what mod they come from.
  * And also make sure you read the respective page for the mod to ensure that it is compatible with MHM.
  * In all likelyhood, you will need a compatability patch for additional mods.
  * Look for compatability patches in MHM AIO or Core Archives, as optional files on mod download pages, or inside downloaded mod archives.


=====================
MAIN SOURCE OF ISSUES
=====================
Make double sure that you have ~NOT~ installed any of LNA file other than "LNA01_99_P.pak"
Make double sure that you have ~NOT~ installed "OXA03_P.pak" from OXA



